  "text": "We also computed effect sizes (ES), which are considered more appropriate than 317 hypothesis testing in single-case research [CITATION_1] . Specifically, we computed Cohen's 318 d effect size to assess whether jugglers' physiological response (i.e., breathing and heart rates) ",
